INSTALL DOCKER

sudo apt update          # Update package list
sudo apt install docker.io -y   # Install Docker
sudo systemctl start docker     # Start Docker service
sudo systemctl enable docker    # Enable Docker to start on boot
docker --version                # Check installed Docker version


View Images & Pull Image

docker images           # List all downloaded Docker images
docker pull ubuntu      # Download the Ubuntu image from Docker Hub


Run a Container

docker run -it --name mycontainer <container_name>   # Start a container interactively


Check Containers

docker ps               # Show running containers
docker ps -a            # Show all containers, including stopped ones


Manage Container Life Cycle

docker stop mycontainer      # Stop a running container
docker start mycontainer     # Start a stopped container
docker restart mycontainer   # Restart a container
docker pause mycontainer     # Pause container processes
docker unpause mycontainer   # Resume paused container


Delete Container

docker stop mycontainer      # Stop the container
docker rm mycontainer        # Remove the container
docker rmi ubuntu            # Remove the image (optional)
